<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#821928"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Compensation<BR>Element</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#821928" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000" BGCOLOR="#821928"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Form&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" BGCOLOR="#821928" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt" BGCOLOR="#821928"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B>Objective</B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size:10pt"><B>FIXED</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center">Base Salary</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">Cash</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL">Market competitive to attract and retain highly qualified leaders</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL">Reflective of individual performance, experience and scope of responsibility</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" ROWSPAN="4" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size:10pt"><B>VARIABLE</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">Annual&nbsp;Executive</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">Incentive Plan</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">(&#147;EIP&#148;)</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Cash</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Motivate executives to achieve annual Company and business segment performance goals</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Stock Options</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Equity</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="3" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Reward executives for delivering on the long-term performance goals aligned with the Enterprise Strategy and creating long-term stockholder value</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Performance- based RSUs (&#147;PRSUs&#148;)</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Equity</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center">Long-Term Incentive Cash (&#147;LTI Cash&#148;)</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000">Cash</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle" ROWSPAN="3" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size:10pt"><B>RETIREMENT AND
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">CHANGE-IN-CONTROL</FONT> BENEFITS</B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">Savings &amp; Investment</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Plan-401(k)</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">Cash</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" ROWSPAN="2" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL">Retirement savings
in both qualified and nonqualified plans aligned with market practices</P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL">Nonqualified plan allows
contributions for those executives exceeding the IRS limits</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Change-in-</FONT> Control Severance Policy</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">Cash/</P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">Provides compensation in the event of a termination after a
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Overview of Key Compensation Decisions </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following describes significant actions taken and any changes made to our executive compensation practices for the NEOs. We believe these practices reflect good
corporate governance in our compensation policies while continuing to recognize and reward superior Company, business segment and individual performance as they align with our Enterprise Strategy objectives. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Annual Executive Incentive Plan (&#147;EIP&#148;) </B> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The EIP awards for 2016 were based solely on the achievement of financial performance measures. This is a change from the 2015 annual incentive plan design, which was based 80&nbsp;percent on financial performance and
20&nbsp;percent on individual performance objectives. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">24 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The 2016 EIP financial performance measures were based 60&nbsp;percent on operating income growth and 40&nbsp;percent on organic revenue growth, which are two critical financial performance metrics aligned with
ITW&#146;s Enterprise Strategy performance goals, as described in the Executive Overview. For corporate executives, the measures were based solely on Company results. For operating executives, the measures were based 50&nbsp;percent on Company
performance and 50&nbsp;percent on the performance of their respective segment. The payout range of the EIP was 0&nbsp;percent to 200&nbsp;percent of target, which will be the same for 2017. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Long-Term Incentives </B> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Weightings of the long-term incentive award components in 2016 remained the same as 2015. The weighting for the CEO was 40&nbsp;percent stock options, 30&nbsp;percent PRSUs and 30&nbsp;percent LTI Cash, and the
weighting for the other NEOs was <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-third</FONT> each for stock options, PRSUs and LTI Cash. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">As noted earlier in the Executive Overview, for the 2016-2018 LTI Cash award, one of the three financial performance measures was changed to EPS from organic revenue growth, which became a substantive performance
measure in the annual incentive plan for 2016. The long-term incentive measures for the 2016-2018 LTI Cash award are operating margin, ROIC and EPS, with each of the three measures equally weighted. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#161;</FONT></SUP>&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="2%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Also noted in the Executive Overview, to ensure alignment with the current phase of the Enterprise Strategy for 2017, we are changing our long-term incentive program mix by increasing options to 50&nbsp;percent of the
award with the remaining 50&nbsp;percent being performance-based awards (25&nbsp;percent payable in cash and 25&nbsp;percent payable in performance share units). The performance-based awards will have the same financial measures as our 2016 LTI Cash
program: operating margin, ROIC and EPS. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>2016 Target Compensation </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our total target compensation (base salary, EIP and long-term incentives) is intended to create a strong correlation between the executive&#146;s compensation and
Company and/or business segment performance. The compensation elements based on Company or business segment performance include EIP, LTI Cash and equity incentives. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Ninety-one</FONT> percent of 2016 total
compensation for the CEO is tied to performance, with 54&nbsp;percent in the form of equity and 37&nbsp;percent in performance cash awards. <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Eighty-one</FONT> percent of 2016 total compensation for the other NEOs (on
average) is tied to performance, with 42&nbsp;percent delivered through equity awards and 39&nbsp;percent in the form of performance cash awards. Our equity and long-term cash awards have multi-year vesting schedules to align the interests of our
executive officers with the long-term interests of our stockholders. The following charts illustrate the allocation of our total target compensation opportunity for 2016 between fixed (base salary) and variable (EIP and long-term incentives)
components. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">25 </P>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">*Total target compensation as used in the charts above is the sum of base salary, target EIP and the grant date fair value of LTI Cash
and equity incentives. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Ongoing Best Practices </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We regularly review and refine our executive compensation program to ensure that it continues to reflect practices and policies that are aligned with our <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">pay-for-performance</FONT></FONT> philosophy and the interests of our stockholders. In this regard, our 2016 compensation program reflects the following: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR BGCOLOR="#821928" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="3" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">What We Do</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" COLSPAN="3" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">What We Don&#146;t
Do</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.40em; text-indent:-2.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">We maintain a Compensation Recovery Policy (&#147;clawback policy&#148;) requiring the reimbursement of incentives if a material financial restatement is
required</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.40em; text-indent:-2.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT
STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">We do not provide executives with employment agreements</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.40em; text-indent:-2.40em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">We have stock ownership guidelines linking the interests of long-term stockholders to our executives and mitigating compensation-related risk</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">We do not provide perquisites or gross ups as part of our
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control</FONT></FONT> agreements</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">The Compensation Committee engages an independent compensation consultant who advises the Committee on regulatory and other current trends and key
developments in executive compensation</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">We do not allow share repricing within our stock option plan</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">The Compensation Committee conducts an annual review of the performance of the CEO as well as the other NEOs</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">We prohibit officers, directors, and employees from hedging, pledging, short selling or publicly trading options involving ITW common
stock</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman">&#10003;</FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">We hold an annual advisory vote for our stockholders to review and approve our executive compensation programs; we are recommending continuing with annual
advisory voting by our stockholders</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"><FONT STYLE="font-family:Times New Roman"><FONT STYLE="FONT-FAMILY:WINGDINGS">&#251;</FONT></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">We do not allow immediate vesting of equity awards that are continued or replaced upon a <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">change-in-control;</FONT></FONT> all such awards allow only double-trigger vesting <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap"><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">(change-in-control</FONT></FONT> and termination)</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">26 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Say On Pay Advisory Voting Results </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2014, 2015 and 2016, 97.6&nbsp;percent, 96.9&nbsp;percent and 95.9&nbsp;percent, respectively, of votes cast approved the compensation of our NEOs. The Committee
believes that this favorable vote is confirmation that our shareholders believe that the pay of our NEOs is appropriately aligned with the performance of the Company and the interests of our shareholders. The Committee therefore determined that no
changes to our executive compensation practices were necessary as a result of the Say on Pay vote. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><A NAME="rom291322_16"></A>How We Make
Compensation Decisions </B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #821928">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Role of the Compensation Committee </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Committee conducts an annual review of ITW&#146;s practices and the compensation of our executive officers to ensure: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The elements of the total compensation package are aligned with the market to attract and retain the caliber of talent required to deliver on our business strategies; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Compensation decisions are meaningfully differentiated to appropriately reflect the contributions of our highest performers; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our incentive programs drive performance aligned with our Enterprise Strategy and the Company&#146;s culture and values. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In making its executive compensation decisions and recommendations, the Committee is guided by the following factors: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Our compensation philosophy; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Compensation comparisons from a peer group of diversified multinational industrial companies with similar size, value, and complexity; and </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Management&#146;s contribution to our short- and long-term goals based on profitable growth and strong returns on capital. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, the Committee engaged an independent advisor, Frederick W. Cook&nbsp;&amp; Co., Inc. (&#147;Cook&#148;), to work directly on its behalf and in cooperation
with management to review ITW&#146;s executive compensation program, confirm appropriateness of our peer companies, and assess our compensation governance process. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">See &#147;Board of Directors and Its Committees &#151; Compensation Committee&#148; under &#147;Proposal&nbsp;1&nbsp;&#151;Election&nbsp;of Directors&#148; for more
information about the function of the Compensation Committee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Role of the Compensation Consultant </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As previously stated, the Committee has engaged Cook as its independent compensation consultant. In 2016, Cook conducted a marketplace review of the compensation we pay
to our executive officers. Cook provided the Committee with relevant market data, including a review of our pay and performance and that of our peers, reviewed the peer companies we use for comparison purposes, and benchmarked our compensation
against our peer companies. Cook also assisted the Committee with its assessment of compensation-related risk. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Based on its consideration of factors under NYSE
listing standards, the Committee concluded that the work performed by Cook and its senior advisor involved in the engagement did not raise any conflict of interest. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">27 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>2016 Risk Assessment </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee, together with management, annually considers potential risks when reviewing our compensation programs for all employees, including our executive officers.
Based on this assessment, the Committee concluded that our 2016 compensation programs do not create risks that are reasonably likely to have a material adverse effect on ITW. In making this determination, the Committee reviewed the key design
elements of our compensation programs, as well as the means by which any potential risks may be mitigated, including: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">A Balanced Mix of Compensation Components &#151; The target compensation mix for our executive officers is composed of salary, annual cash incentives and long-term cash and equity incentives, representing a mix that is
not overly weighted toward short-term cash incentives. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Multiple Performance Factors &#151; Our incentive compensation plans use Company-wide measures, which encourage focus on the achievement of objectives for the overall benefit of the Company. Multiple financial goals
also prevent an overemphasis on any one metric. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Long-term Incentives &#151; Our long-term incentives are primarily equity-based, and our long-term cash program is subject to performance goals. These long-term incentives have three-year vesting schedules (PRSUs and
long-term cash) or four-year vesting schedules (stock options), in each case to complement our annual cash-based incentives. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Capped Incentive Awards &#151; Annual incentive awards are capped at 200&nbsp;percent of target, while our long-term cash awards are capped at 150&nbsp;percent of target. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Stock Ownership Guidelines &#151; Our guidelines call for significant share ownership, which further aligns the interests of our executive officers with the long-term interests of our stockholders. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Clawback Policy &#151; Our Clawback Policy authorizes the Committee to recoup past incentive compensation in the event of a material restatement of the Company&#146;s financial results. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Prohibition on Hedging and Pledging &#151; Employees are subject to Company policy that prohibits pledging and hedging activities with respect to ITW stock. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Committee Oversight &#151; The Committee has ultimate authority to determine, and reduce if appropriate, compensation provided to our executive officers. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="2%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">&#149;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Independent Compensation Consultant &#151; The Committee retains an outside independent compensation consultant. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Peer Companies </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee has identified a group of comparable companies, which we refer to as the peer group, to benchmark
executive compensation and provide </P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="50%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="48%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">competitive market data to be used in establishing and recommending each element of compensation. The peer group is reviewed annually by the Committee
with assistance from Cook. In addition, the Committee refers to market data based on manufacturing companies within the Aon Hewitt TCM Online Executive survey using regression analysis and tabular long-term incentive data and the Mercer Executive
Compensation survey with a revenue range of $5&nbsp;billion to $20&nbsp;billion for corporate executives and $1.2&nbsp;billion to $2.375&nbsp;billion for the operating executives.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:2.00pt solid #821928; BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #821928">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:2.00pt solid #821928; BORDER-RIGHT:2.00pt solid #821928; padding-right:2pt"> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:0.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Peer&nbsp;Group&nbsp;Selection&nbsp;Criteria:</B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;U.S. publicly traded companies from ITW&#146;s same and related industries, identified based on
Standard&nbsp;&amp; Poor&#146;s Global Industry Classification Standard (GICS) codes;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.50em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Companies with <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">one-fourth</FONT> to four times our revenue and
market capitalization with broadly similar businesses and pay models;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Companies that compete for the same customers with similar products and/or services; and</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom">In connection with its annual review in 2016, the Committee removed Danaher Corporation from the</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:2.00pt solid #821928; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #821928">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:2.00pt solid #821928; BORDER-BOTTOM:2.00pt solid #821928; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.00em; text-indent:-1.20em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&#149;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Companies with whom we may compete for executive talent.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt; margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt">&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">28 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Company&#146;s peer group due to Danaher&#146;s <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">spin-off</FONT> of several business
segments in 2016, including the Industrial Technologies and Test&nbsp;&amp; Measurement segments. As such, Danaher no longer meets the peer group criteria. For 2016, the Committee identified the following 18 companies to be used as the
Company&#146;s peer group: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="89.6%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">At the time of the Committee&#146;s review, the revenue median of the peer group was $16.8&nbsp;billion based on the latest four
quarters, and the median market capitalization was $22.9&nbsp;billion, versus $13.5&nbsp;billion and $40.0&nbsp;billion, respectively, for ITW. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The nature of our
decentralized and diverse lines of business presents challenges in identifying similar organizations for comparison purposes; however, we believe that the peer group selected provides relevant comparisons. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Compensation Decisions and Individual Compensation Levels </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On an annual basis, the CEO reviews the total compensation of the named executive officers and makes recommendations to the Committee based on his assessment of each
executive&#146;s individual performance and the peer group compensation information. The Committee makes recommendations to the independent directors regarding the CEO&#146;s compensation based on an assessment of the CEO&#146;s performance and the
peer group compensation information. There are no material differences in the policies and decision processes used in setting compensation for the CEO and the other NEOs. However, the different levels of compensation for the NEOs, as shown in the
Summary Compensation Table of this proxy statement, reflect internal factors such as each executive&#146;s scope of responsibility, performance, impact on profitable growth and breadth of experience, as well as compensation data from the peer group.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><A NAME="rom291322_17"></A>Components of the 2016 Executive Compensation Program </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #821928">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Base Salary </I></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In determining base salary, the CEO and the Committee consider the size and scope of the executive officers&#146; responsibilities, experience, performance, and the
median base salary of similar positions at our peer group companies. The Committee believes that median base salary is an appropriate general reference point to use for encouraging solid performance. Base salaries are reviewed annually, and
adjustments are intended to recognize performance and contributions over the prior year, as well as any significant changes in duties or scope of responsibility. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In
February 2016, the Compensation Committee reviewed Mr.&nbsp;Santi&#146;s performance and approved a base salary increase to $1,212,640 from $1,166,000 (4 percent). For the other NEOs, the Committee approved recommended base pay increases that ranged
between 3.8&nbsp;percent and 4.5&nbsp;percent. These base salary increases were effective February 29, 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Annual Executive Incentive
Plan </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that executives generally should be rewarded for their contributions to the overall financial success measured by income and organic
growth of the Company as a whole and, if applicable, the business segment he or she leads. Achieving our annual financial objectives is important to executing our current strategic objectives and delivering long-term value to stockholders. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">29 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee determines and approves the performance results and awards for the NEOs and recommends for approval, and the
independent directors of the full Board approve, the annual incentive award amount for the CEO. As previously noted, for 2016, the EIP was changed to be composed solely of financial performance measures for our NEOs. The financial metric weighting
for the CEO, Vice Chairmen, and CFO was based 60&nbsp;percent on Company operating income and 40&nbsp;percent on Company organic revenue growth. For operating executives, the weighting of the financial measures was based 60&nbsp;percent on operating
income and 40&nbsp;percent on organic revenue growth, with 50&nbsp;percent of each metric based on Company results and 50&nbsp;percent on results of their respective business segment. These weightings are intended to align the operating executives
with the achievement of both segment and Company-wide financial performance objectives. The financial measures were recommended by management and approved by the Committee at the start of the 2016 performance year. The Committee has the discretion
to make adjustments in the calculation of financial performance to eliminate factors beyond the control of management and to eliminate possible disincentives to act in the long-term best interests of the Company and our stockholders. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2016 EIP Financial Measures </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For 2016, executive officers were eligible
to earn a payment according to the performance scales below. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:4%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2016 EIP Company Financial Targets </B></P>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that ensuring the long-term growth and profitability of the business is a primary management responsibility. Therefore, a significant portion of an executive
officer&#146;s compensation should be directly linked to key financial performance measures that consider the long-term perspective, such as operating margin, ROIC, EPS and ITW&#146;s stock performance over time.</P></TD></TR>

</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For 2016, our NEOs received stock options, PRSUs, and LTI Cash awards. We believe that stock options are an effective incentive because
they directly align the interests of the executives with those of our stockholders, as an unexercised stock option has no realizable value if our stock price falls below the exercise price, while the value increases along with increases in our stock
price above the exercise price. The stock option awards are combined with PRSUs and LTI Cash to more closely align long-term incentives with our Enterprise Strategy objectives and increase emphasis on key financial performance measures. The
weightings of the total target values of the 2016 long-term incentive equity and cash awards were as follows: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:15%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2016 Long-Term Incentive Award

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">31 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee has established specific vesting and expiration provisions associated with termination of employment due to
death, disability and retirement, as defined in the applicable awards, and forfeiture provisions upon other termination of employment. The Committee, in its sole discretion, may deem a long-term incentive award, whether vested or unvested, to be
immediately forfeited if the recipient competes with the Company, engages in gross misconduct or conduct that is against the business interests of the Company, or divulges confidential information about the Company to others. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2016 Stock Option Awards </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The 2016 stock options vest in equal
installments over a four-year period ending in 2020. Stock options are awarded with an exercise price equal to the fair market value of the common stock on the date of grant and normally expire ten years after the award date. We currently award only
<FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> stock options because we believe that the tax benefits to the Company of <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-qualified</FONT> stock options outweigh the potential tax benefits to the NEOs of
incentive stock options. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2016 Performance-Based RSU Awards </I></B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">PRSUs
vest three years from the date of award, subject to the achievement of the performance goal set at the beginning of the performance period. PRSUs are awarded based on the fair market value of one share of ITW common stock on the date of award. The
payout range is 10&nbsp;percent to 100&nbsp;percent of the target award. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">For PRSUs awarded in 2016, the performance goal is based on cumulative EPS from continuing
operations over a three-year performance period (2016 through 2018) based on a sliding scale. The target/maximum is $11.55 cumulative EPS over the three-year performance period, and the achievement of the target/maximum will result in a payout of
the maximum number of shares subject to the PRSU. If less than $9.55 cumulative EPS is achieved, none of these PRSUs will vest. If EPS growth is at or above the $9.55 threshold but below the $11.55 target/maximum, the awards will vest in proportion
to the level of EPS achieved. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2016 Long-Term Incentive Cash Awards </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In February 2016, our NEOs received an annual LTI Cash award with a three-year performance period. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The goals for the 2016 LTI Cash awards are equally weighted and based on operating margin, ROIC and EPS. The payout at the end of the performance period will be based on
the following sliding payout scale: </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:7%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2016 LTI Cash Payout Scale </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="72%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:9pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="38%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="11%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="2%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="10%"></TD>

<TD WIDTH="8%"></TD>

<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Operating</FONT></B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Margin</FONT></B></FONT></P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>2014 Long-Term Incentive Cash Award Payouts </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The LTI Cash award granted in 2014 under the Long-Term Incentive Cash Plan in effect at that time (with a three-year performance period ended December&nbsp;31, 2016) was
based in equal parts on operating margin, ROIC and organic revenue growth (calculated using a simple average as reported in our financial statements as of the time financial results for each year were publicly released). </P>

<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Sundaram
Nagarajan</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">$416,667</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">117.8%</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">$490,833</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B><I>Timing of Long-Term Incentive Awards </I></B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee meets in February of each year following the Company&#146;s public release of its earnings results for the recently completed fiscal year to consider and
act with respect to long-term incentive awards for the executive officers. Long-term awards are made in compliance with the Long-Term Incentive Plan, including the requirement that stock options may not be awarded at less than 100&nbsp;percent of
the fair market value of ITW&#146;s common stock on the date of award. The exercise price of the awards is based on the closing price of ITW&#146;s stock on the date of award. We do not time awards for the purpose of enhancing the value of executive
compensation. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">33 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><A NAME="rom291322_18"></A>Executive Compensation Policies and Guidelines </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #821928">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Stock Ownership Guidelines and
Hedging Policy </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that stock ownership is important because it aligns the interests of our management and directors with those of our
stockholders. Because of the importance of stock ownership, the Board of Directors and the Committee have adopted stock ownership guidelines for executive officers and directors. The 2016 guidelines for stock ownership as a multiple of executive
officers&#146; base salaries and of directors&#146; annual retainers are as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="49%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="4%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="47%"></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#821928" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Title</FONT></B></FONT></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ALIGN="center" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000; BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt"><FONT COLOR="#ffffff"><B><FONT COLOR="#ffffff">Guideline</FONT></B></FONT></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chief Executive
Officer</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">6 times salary</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt">Vice Chairmen, Executive Vice Presidents, and Chief Financial Officer</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="middle" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">3 times salary</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Senior Vice
Presidents</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">2 times salary</TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#d8d8d8" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-left:8pt"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">Non-employee</FONT> Directors</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #000000; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000; padding-right:2pt">5 times annual retainer</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Committee expects that an executive officer or <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> director will achieve the
applicable ownership level within five years. The achievement of these guidelines is reviewed annually. The Board believes that its stock ownership guidelines are appropriate, reasonable and attainable given the responsibilities and compensation
levels of our executive officers and directors and has not deemed it necessary to impose a holding period requirement for shares owned by our executive officers and directors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All NEOs and directors who have been in their positions for five or more years have met or exceeded the applicable 2016 stock ownership guideline. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All recipients of Company equity-based awards, which include key employees and all officers and directors, are subject to our policy against options trading and short
sales of ITW stock, as well as trading in derivatives linked to Company stock. In addition, since April 2013, our employees (including NEOs) and <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-employee</FONT> directors are prohibited from pledging Company
stock, and pledged shares are excluded from ownership for purposes of our stock ownership guidelines. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Compensation Recovery Policy
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We maintain a Compensation Recovery Policy (a &#147;clawback policy&#148;) applicable to all executive officers of the Company subject to
Section&nbsp;16 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934. Under the policy, the Committee will seek reimbursement of incentives paid to executive officers where the payment was predicated upon the achievement of certain financial results with respect
to the applicable performance period that were subsequently the subject of a material restatement due to material <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">non-compliance</FONT> of the Company with any financial reporting requirement under the U.S.
securities laws. The reimbursement amount is equal to the excess of the gross incentive payment made over the gross payment that would have been made if the original payment had been determined based on the restated financial results. Further,
following a material restatement of our financial statements, we will seek reimbursement of compensation and profits from trading in Company stock received by our CEO and CFO to the extent required under Section&nbsp;304 of the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of
2002. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>Deductibility </I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Internal Revenue
Code Section&nbsp;162(m) limits the deductibility of compensation in excess of $1,000,000 paid to the NEOs. Performance-based compensation, as defined in the regulations under Section&nbsp;162(m), is exempt from this limit. In 2011, our stockholders
approved the 2011 Cash Incentive Plan to provide a means to pay performance-based short and long-term incentive cash compensation </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">34 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
that qualifies for the exemption under Section&nbsp;162(m). Executives whose compensation may be subject to the limits of 162(m) initially receive annual and long-term cash incentive awards
pursuant to the 2011 Cash Incentive Plan subject to performance goals designed to comply with the requirements of Section&nbsp;162(m). The Committee then exercises its negative discretion to adjust the awards to the level of bonus calculated
pursuant to the performance goals set in connection with the underlying bonus programs, described above under &#147;Annual Executive Incentive Plan&#148; and &#147;Long-Term Incentives &#150; 2016 Long-Term Incentive Cash Awards.&#148; This
procedure better enables the Company to assure the deductibility of the annual and long-term cash performance incentive payments. The Committee recognizes its obligation to reward performance that increases stockholder value and retains the
flexibility in its discretion to award compensation that does not qualify for the 162(m) exemption if it believes that to be in the best interests of stockholders. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">35 </P>

relevant year, and the assumptions applicable to these valuations can be found in Note 12 of the Notes to Financial Statements &#151; Stock-Based Compensation contained in the Illinois Tool Works Inc. Annual Report on Form <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">10-K</FONT> for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

thereunder can be found above under &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis &#151; Components of the 2016 Executive Compensation Program &#150; Annual Executive Incentive Plan&#148; and &#147;&#150;&nbsp;Long-Term Incentives.&#148;

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">These amounts include an amount of interest in the applicable calendar year considered to be in excess of market rates credited to the deferred compensation accounts of the NEOs under the ECRIP, discussed in more detail
under &#147;Nonqualified Deferred Compensation&#148; below. When a participant attains retirement eligibility at age 55 and 10 years of service, any amounts in his or her ECRIP account deferred prior to January&nbsp;1, 2010 are entitled to a return
of 130&nbsp;percent of the monthly Moody&#146;s Corporate Bond Yield Average rate, and the excess interest portion is deemed to be amounts exceeding 100&nbsp;percent of such rate. This additional interest credit applies to all eligible plan
participants, including the NEOs. All amounts deferred after December&nbsp;31, 2009 accrue interest at 100&nbsp;percent of the Moody&#146;s Rate. The individual amounts of pension benefits and excess interest credits earned in each year are shown in
the table below. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3%; margin-right:9%; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>**Mr.&nbsp;O&#146;Herlihy participated in the ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan from 1989 through 1999. From 1999 through August 2011,
he was employed in Ireland, participated in the ITW Irish Pension Plan and ceased active participation in the U.S. plan. Upon his return to the U.S. in 2011, he was ineligible to actively participate in the U.S. plan due to the plan participation
closure effective January&nbsp;1, 2007. The ITW Irish Pension Plan accrual is included in the &#147;Accrual in ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan&#148; column above, because this amount also represents a qualified pension plan present value. For 2015,
the reduction in the present value of accumulated benefits reflects the economic adjustment in the value of his benefits. </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:3%; margin-right:9%; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>***
Mr.&nbsp;Nagarajan became an NEO in 2016; therefore, prior years are not presented. </I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">For 2016, the Company contributions to the ECRIP and the Savings and Investment Plan, based on plan rules for all eligible participants, are shown. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The range of potential share distributions under the 2016 PRSU award for the NEOs as set by the Committee in February 2016 for performance for the three-year period 2016 through 2018 is set forth in these columns. The
&#147;Threshold&#148; estimated future payout is based on achievement of $9.55 cumulative earnings per share (EPS) from continuing operations over the three-year performance period. The &#147;Target/Maximum&#148; performance goal is $11.55
cumulative EPS from continuing operations over the three-year performance period, and achievement of the target/maximum will result in a payout of the maximum number of shares subject to the PRSU. If cumulative EPS is above the $9.55 threshold but
below the $11.55 target/maximum, the awards will vest in proportion to the level of EPS achieved. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:2pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(5)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Grant date fair values of options awarded to the NEOs on February&nbsp;12, 2016 were based on an implied value of $20.02 per share as determined using a binomial valuation technique under Accounting Standards
Codification Topic 718. Grant date fair value of PRSUs was based on the assumption that the performance conditions will be met. </TD></TR></TABLE>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><A NAME="rom291322_23"></A>Option Exercises and Stock Vested </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #821928">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following table provides information regarding option
exercises and stock vesting for each NEO during 2016. The value realized upon the exercise of options is calculated using the difference between the option exercise price and the market price at the time of exercise multiplied by the number of
shares underlying the option. The value realized upon the vesting of stock awards is based on the market price on the vesting date. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center">40 </P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:11pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><A NAME="rom291322_25"></A>ITW Retirement Plans </B></FONT></P>
<P STYLE="line-height:4.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:2.00pt solid #821928">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#821928"><B><I>ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan
</I></B></FONT></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:9pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We maintain the ITW Retirement Accumulation Plan (the &#147;Pension Plan&#148;) for the benefit of eligible employees of participating U.S.
businesses to provide a portion of the income necessary for retirement. The Pension Plan was closed to new entrants effective January&nbsp;1, 2007. The Pension Plan is structured as a &#147;pension equity plan&#148; under which a participant
accumulates an <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">age-based</FONT> percentage for each year of plan participation. The sum of the Accumulated Percentages multiplied by final average annual pay (generally, salary and annual incentive paid in the
highest five years out of the last ten complete calendar years of service), plus the sum of the Excess Percentages multiplied by the final average annual pay above the Covered Compensation, produce an amount that can be received as a <FONT
STYLE="white-space:nowrap">lump-sum</FONT> payment or an actuarially equivalent lifetime annuity. For each year of credited service after December&nbsp;31, 2000, the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">age-based</FONT> percentages are as follows: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:9pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
